    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Pottery found predominantly in the Diyala region of Mesopotamia at the start of the Early Dynastic period from about 2900 to 2750 BCE; characterized by generally large, broad-shouldered pots with painted red designs, often outlined in black, on a buff or yellow ground.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
